    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "hmm, I think it should still if for example the dir already contains a README or license etc.\r\n\r\nBut yeah the problem is that we do a blind `git add .` which also adds inner repos, we should scan nested existing dirs (not called `lib`) and fail with we encounter a git repo\r\n\r\n```error: `forge init` cannot be run on existing git workspaces```\r\n\r\nalso suggesting some flags for init\r\n\r\n`--no-vcs` or `--no-git` to not initialize a new git repo.\r\n`-q, --quite` to not print anything\r\n`--offline` do not pull anything from network (ds-test, forge-std)\r\n`--bare` or `--no-commit` do not commit initial commit",
